ay于1340年出生在英国越可爾吉可林頓时，她的父亲William Mowbray V of Barton6岁，母亲Margaret Chaumont26岁。她于大约1386年与Sir William Gascoigne I在英国越可爾结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。她去世于1391年在英国越可爾希亞活享年51岁，埋葬在英国越可爾希亞活。"},"hr":{"1340–1391":"1340.–1391.","1348–Female":"1348–preminula","1350–1419":"1350–1419","1386–1422":"1386–1422","1335–1391":"1335–1391.","1315–Female":"1315–preminula","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1335":"1335","1422":"1422","1386":"1386","1340":"1340.","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1419":"1419","about 1386":"oko 1386.","1391":"1391.","Kirklington, Yorkshire, England":"Kirklington, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England":"Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England","Harewood, Yorkshire, England":"Harewood, Yorkshire, England"},"cs":{"1340–1391":"1340–1391","1348–Female":"1348–Zesnulá","1350–1419":"1350–1419","1386–1422":"1386–1422","1335–1391":"1335–1391","1315–Female":"1315–Zesnulá","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1335":"1335","1422":"1422","1386":"1386","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1419":"1419","about 1386":"okolo 1386","1391":"1391","Kirklington, Yorkshire, England":"Kirklington, Yorkshire, Anglie","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Anglie","Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England":"Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, Anglie","Harewood, Yorkshire, England":"Harewood, Yorkshire, Anglie"},"da":{"1340–1391":"1340–1391","1348–Female":"1348–Afdød","1350–1419":"1350–1419","1386–1422":"1386–1422","1335–1391":"1335–1391","1315–Female":"1315–Afdød","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1335":"1335","1422":"1422","1386":"1386","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1419":"1419","about 1386":"omkring 1386","1391":"1391","Kirklington, Yorkshire, England":"Kirklington, Jórvík, England","Yorkshire, England":"Jórvík, England","Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England":"Gawthorpe, Jórvík, England","Harewood, Yorkshire, England":"Harewood, Jórvík, England"},"nl":{"1340–1391":"1340–1391","1348–Female":"1348–Overleden","1350–1419":"1350–1419","1386–1422":"1386–1422","1335–1391":"1335–1391","1315–Female":"1315–Overleden","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1335":"1335","1422":"1422","1386":"1386","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1419":"1419","about 1386":"circa 1386","1391":"1391","Kirklington, Yorkshire, England":"Kirklington, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England":"Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England","Harewood, Yorkshire, England":"Harewood, Yorkshire, England"},"en":{"1340–1391":"1340–1391","1348–Female":"1348–Deceased","1350–1419":"1350–1419","1386–1422":"1386–1422","1335–1391":"1335–1391","1315–Female":"1315–Deceased","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1335":"1335","1422":"1422","1386":"1386","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1419":"1419","about 1386":"about 1386","1391":"1391","Kirklington, Yorkshire, England":"Kirklington, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England":"Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England","Harewood, Yorkshire, England":"Harewood, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Mowbray","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (northern; of Norman origin): habitational name from Montbray (Manche). Robert <i>de Mowbray</i> was Earl of Northumbria 1086–95, but was later imprisoned and deposed for rebelling against William II."],"variants":[{"name":"Mulberry","meanings":["English (Middlesex and Cambridgeshire): variant of   Mowbray  .","Irish (Derry): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Maoilbhearaigh</b> ‘descendant of the devotee of (Saint) <i>Bearach</i>’."]},{"name":"Moubray","meanings":["English: variant of   Mowbray  ."]},{"name":"Mayberry","meanings":["English: most probably an altered form of   Mowbray  . It is also found as   Maybury  , which has the form of an English habitational name. There is a place near Woking in Surrey so called; however, this is not recorded until 1885 and is probably derived from the surname. In England this surname is found mainly in the West Midlands; it has also spread into Wales. In Ireland this form is common in Ulster; MacLysaght records that it was taken there from England in the 17th century."]},{"name":"Memory","meanings":["English: variant of   Mowbray  ."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":42,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth Mowbray was born in 1340, in Kirklington, Yorkshire, England, her father, William Mowbray V of Barton, was 6 and her mother, Margaret Chaumont, was 26. She married Sir William Gascoigne I about 1386, in Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1391, in Harewood, Yorkshire, England, at the age of 51, and was buried in Harewood, Yorkshire, England."},"et":{"1340–1391":"1340–1391","1348–Female":"1348–Surnud","1350–1419":"1350–1419","1386–1422":"1386–1422","1335–1391":"1335–1391","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1335":"1335","1422":"1422","1386":"1386","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1419":"1419","about 1386":"umbes 1386","1391":"1391","Kirklington, Yorkshire, England":"Kirklington, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England":"Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England","Harewood, Yorkshire, England":"Harewood, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1340–1391":"1340–1391","1348–Female":"1348–Kuollut","1350–1419":"1350–1419","1386–1422":"1386–1422","1335–1391":"1335–1391","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1335":"1335","1422":"1422","1386":"1386","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1419":"1419","about 1386":"noin 1386","1391":"1391","Kirklington, Yorkshire, England":"Kirklington, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England":"Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England","Harewood, Yorkshire, England":"Harewood, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1340–1391":"1340–1391","1348–Female":"1348–Décédée","1350–1419":"1350–1419","1386–1422":"1386–1422","1335–1391":"1335–1391","1315–Female":"1315–Décédée","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1335":"1335","1422":"1422","1386":"1386","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1419":"1419","about 1386":"environ 1386","1391":"1391","Kirklington, Yorkshire, England":"Kirklington, Everwyck, Angleterre","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre","Gawthorpe, Yorkshire, England":"Gawthorpe, Everwyck, Angleterre","Harewood, Yorkshire, England":"Hare